cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.CE

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper proposes a novel network-coding scheme for MIMO two-way relay channels, which involves encoding and decoding of information. This falls under the scope of information theory.
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with the design of a network-coding scheme for a relay network, which involves the use of multiple antennas at the users and the relay. This falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture.
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper involves the design of a system for relaying information between two users using a multi-antenna relay. This falls under the scope of systems and control.
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with the transmission of multiple streams of information between two users using a multi-antenna relay. This falls under the scope of multimedia.
5. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) - The paper involves the use of mathematical techniques to analyze the performance of the proposed network-coding scheme. This falls under the scope of computational engineering, finance, and science.
